n both total and reduced glutathione content (Khand et al, 2001).    sod2-/- (mitochondrial SOD) mice treated with antioxidants EUK-8, EUK134 and EU-189 show reduced lethal and neurodegenerative effects of excess superoxide generation (Hinderfield et al, 2004).      Overexpression of MnSOD in diabetic mice prevented: (i) the diabetes-induced decreases in retinal glutathione concentration and total antioxidant capacity, and (ii) the diabetes-induced increases in the levels of 8-hydroxy 2&#39;-deoxyguanosine and nitrotyrosine, all markers of oxidative stress (Kowluru et al, 2006).     Further evidence is cited in Indo et al (2015).", "timestamp": "Mon Jun 08 15:48:33 +0000 2026"}